===Etymology===
Attested since about 1300, from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|almande|almande, amande|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|VL.|en}} {{m|la|*amendla|*amendla, amandula}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|amygdala|lang=la}}, from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|ἀμυγδάλη|sc=polytonic|lang=grc}}, of uncertain origin. Influenced by {{m|la|amandus}} and by many French and Spanish words of Arabic origin that began with the Arabic definite article ''al-''.<ref>{{R:Etymonline}}</ref>

